thread.title: FedEx quarterly earnings rise, miss Wall Street estimates
thread.title_full: FedEx quarterly earnings rise, miss Wall Street estimates | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: FedEx quarterly earnings rise, miss Wall Street estimates
text:
CHICAGO Package delivery company FedEx Corp ( FDX.N ) on Wednesday reported a higher quarterly net profit, but missed Wall Street estimates as weak global economic conditions and the strong U.S. dollar weighed on results.
The Memphis-based company reported a fiscal 2016 first-quarter net profit of $692 million or $2.42 per share, up 6 percent from $653 million or $2.26 per share a year earlier.
Analysts had on average expected earnings per share of $2.46.
(Reporting By Nick Carey Editing by W Simon)
